    "description": "<p><em>Local Reality Error Spark</em></p><p>The summoner invokes the Ub code and condenses accumulated magitechnical disturbance into an eater. Its power depends on the level of disturbance (decided by the referee or a [[/r d10]] roll). After the eater emerges, the local disturbance reduces one step; stuckforces loosen, energy snarls fade, radiation ghosts dim.</p><ul><li><p>&lt;1 undisturbed: </p><ul><li><p><strong>sparkly air plankton</strong> (L0, harmless)</p></li></ul></li><li><p>1–3 barely disturbed:</p><ul><li><p><strong>purifier slime</strong> (L[[/r 1d4]], caustic)</p></li></ul></li><li><p>4–7 temporal static: </p><ul><li><p><strong>destruction lizard</strong> (L[[/r 2d4]], armored)</p></li></ul></li><li><p>8–9 spatial scarring: </p><ul><li><p><strong>flaming leaper</strong> (L[[/r 2d6]], thorned)</p></li></ul></li><li><p>10+ reality fracture: </p><ul><li><p><strong>blade harvester</strong> (L[[/r 3d4+2]], winged)</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
